cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.MM

The paper deals with the problem of image recognition, specifically in the context of zero-shot learning. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The proposed method involves constructing image samples using a cognitive process, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The method also involves selecting high-quality samples using dissimilarity representation, which is a machine learning technique and falls under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of attributes, which is a common technique in natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the experiments are conducted on benchmark datasets, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM).
